Plants were evaluated for traits: Days from sowing to anthesis defined as when exerted anthers first became visible (DTA); days from sowing to maturity defined as 95 % spike senescence visually scored (DTM); grain filling duration defined as DTM minus DTA (GFD); days from anthesis to 95 % flag leaf senescence visually scored (FLSe); flag leaf width at the widest point (FW) and length of the blade (FL) measured at 10 days after anthesis; relative chlorophyll content of the flag leaf measured using a portable SPAD meter (SPAD-502; Minolta Co. Ltd., Japan) at 10, 13 and 27 days after anthesis, corresponding to directly before and after treatment and at 14 days after treatment, respectively (ChlC10DAA, ChlC13DAA and ChlC27DAA); the area under the curve of the three SPAD readings (AUSC) calculated with the formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
